Package nl.naturalis.geneious.seq

Class SequenceInfoProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.naturalis.geneious.seq.SequenceInfoProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    class SequenceInfoProvider
extends Object
implements AutoCloseable
    Separates AB1 files from fasta files and then calls the FastaFileSplitter to split the fasta files into individual nucleotide sequences. Note that this is an Autocloseable class. You SHOULD create instances of it using a try-with-resources block. This will ensure that the temporary files created by the FastaFileSplitter will be deleted once the import completes. FastaFileSplitter.

    • Field Detail

      • MAX_FASTAS_IN_MEMORY

        static final int MAX_FASTAS_IN_MEMORY
        The maximum number of user-selected fasta files that will be dealt with in-memory (500). If the user selects more than this number of fasta files, or if he/she has disabled fasta file caching in the Prefences panel, the individual nucleotide sequences will be written to temporary files, otherwise they will be processed in-memory.
